Your character is a **Druid** with the **Shaman** ascendancy, level **87**, using **Prolonged Duration I** (actually a support gem, not a skill — main active appears to be `Rampage` or `Furious Slam`).

The sharpest wound in your defenses is `chaos:22%` resistance — you sit **53 percentage points below the 75% cap**. In PoE2, endgame map modifiers and chaos-damage encounters (Breach, Ritual, Trial of Chaos, chaos-dealing boss projectiles) punch through this gap without mercy. Your chaos max-hit is `3,247` — a chaos spike from a T15+ rare or a Trial of Chaos totem will one-shot you through your `2,493` life pool. Elemental resistances (`fire:77%`, `cold:75%`, `lit:75%`) are capped; this is your single defensive bottleneck.

**Suggestion 1: Swap one ring for a rare Lazuli Ring or second Amethyst Ring with explicit +chaos resistance.**

You already wear a rare Amethyst Ring (`Morbid Band`, `+9%` implicit chaos res, `+71` life). Replace your `Woe Gyre` (Iron Ring) with a second rare ⟦panel*:item-card:Lazuli Ring (chaos res)⟧ carrying `+(35–40)% to Chaos Resistance` as a suffix plus life. Lazuli Ring has a `+(20–30)` mana implicit — useful for your mana sustain (`623` current pool). This single swap adds `~31%` chaos res (implicit + explicit combined with a second base), pushing you to `~53%` total — still under cap but no longer one-shot territory.

**Trade-off:** You lose `Woe Gyre`'s `+5 to 9` added physical damage to attacks and `+56` accuracy, which barely register on your `55k` combined DPS. The ring slot is pure stat stick for you — swapping to a chaos-res rare is a defensive upgrade with no offensive downside.

**Suggestion 2: Reserve 30 Spirit for the Impurity aura ⟦panel:gem-detail:Impurity aura⟧.**

`Impurity` is a persistent aura that grants `+(10–29)% to Chaos Resistance` at gem levels 1–20, plus `+(0.3–6)%` from quality. At level 20 with 20% quality you gain `+35%` chaos res to you and allies in presence. You currently reserve `160/160` Spirit (Herald of Ash, likely). Drop one reservation or reallocate Spirit from the passive tree or gear to fit `Impurity` — this pushes chaos res from `22%` to `~57%` baseline, and combined with the ring swap above would cap you at `~75%`.

**Trade-off:** Spirit is scarce in PoE2. If you drop `Herald of Ash` to make room, you lose its `Overkill` burn proliferation and added fire damage — a clear-speed hit. Alternatively, find `+Spirit` on gear (your chest `Pain Shroud` has `+46`, your amulet `Hate Choker` has `+14`) or allocate passive nodes granting Spirit to run both. `Impurity` has no damage scaling unlike offensive auras, so it's purely defensive spend.

