You are a **Druid**, exile — level 87, of the **Shaman** ascendancy. Your archetype is a self-cast life-based melee-caster hybrid. Your main skill is `Prolonged Duration I` (a support-gem aura that extends buff durations) applied to your `Furious Slam` setup — a shapeshift Bear slam linked with cold conversion, freeze, life leech, and `Bhatair's Vengeance`. Your build deals about **55k combined DPS** with a trinity resonance stack, and you sustain rage through `Furious Wellspring` and `Charge Regulation`.

The defensive picture tells a more troubling story. Your elemental resistances are fine — `fire:77%`, `cold:75%`, `lit:75%` — but your **chaos resistance sits at `chaos:22%`**, and your **life pool is only `2,493`**. The PoE2 wiki confirms that the default cap is `75%` for chaos resistance, the same as elemental. At `22%` you are taking **more than three times** the chaos damage you should be. With a `chaos_max_hit` of only **3,247**, a single chaos-volley from an endgame map rare (area level 65+, where the game imposes a `-60%` elemental penalty though chaos has no such campaign penalty) will likely send you to the respawn screen. Your **physical max hit is only 3,753** as well — but chaos is the more urgent gap because it is so far from cap and there are fewer incidental chaos sources on the tree to fix it for free.

Here are two ways to mend it.

**Suggestion 1 — Amethyst Ring swap on the suffix line.** Your ring `Woe Gyre` (Iron Ring base) gives `cold:22%` resistance, `+70 life`, and mana regen — solid, but you are already cold-capped. Swap your other ring (`Morbid Band`, Amethyst base) to a rare **Amethyst Ring** (which has an implicit `+9%` to chaos resistance baked in) with a tier-1 or tier-2 chaos resistance suffix at the top of its explicit mods. An Amethyst Ring base with `+30%` chaos resistance and `+80` life costs you nothing on the passive tree and frees you from the *Morbid Band*'s mediocre `cold:26%` + `+12.9 life regen`. The trade-off: you lose the `+16 Strength` and the `cold:26%` from *Morbid Band*, but you are already cold-capped without it — check your sheet — so that cold roll is dead weight. If you shop for a ring with an open prefix, you can craft `+31%` chaos resistance via the Chaos Orb bench craft (PoE2's crafting bench), slotting you at roughly `53%` chaos — a full **31% less chaos damage taken** over current.

**Suggestion 2 — allocate the Shaman ascendancy notable `Reactive Growth` + `Avatar of Evolution` (if you have not already).** The Shaman wiki page describes `Reactive Growth` as: *"Adapt to the highest Elemental Damage Type of each Hit you take. 10% less Damage taken of each Elemental Damage Type per matching Adaptation. 10% less Elemental Damage taken."* `Avatar of Evolution` doubles the Adaptation effect to 20% per stack and extends duration to 5 seconds, plus converts **5% of Phys taken as each element** (15% phys→element total). This does not directly fix chaos resistance, but it makes every elemental hit that reaches you 10% weaker baseline, and if you get hit repeatedly by the same element, each stack reduces that element's damage by a multiplicative 10%. The trade-off: these nodes cost you **two notable slots** in the Shaman tree, which means giving up either `Turning of the Seasons` (exposure + extra damage) or `Sacred Flow` (spirit per empty charm slot). For a life-based build with `2,493` life, the flat **10% less elemental damage taken** from Reactive Growth alone is more valuable than exposure on enemies you cannot keep in your presence. Worth considering when you have your next 4 ascendancy points.

**Synergies:**
- `Palm of the Dreamer` (unique Shrine Sceptre) — grants the `Impurity` persistent aura skill at level 15–20 (up to `+29%` chaos resistance to you and allies). Socket it with `Vitality I` for life regen. The downside: you lose your current two-handed weapon and must re-evaluate your skill setup around a one-handed + focus/shield. A major rebuild, but the single biggest chaos-res bandage available.
- Chaos resistance on jewels — a single sapphire jewel with a chaos resistance suffix (`+12–16%`) in one of your passive-tree jewel sockets gives immediate breathing room with zero opportunity cost to gear slots.

